children.name: Tags are used for items that need to be labeled, categorized, or organized using keywords that describe them. Tags are also used for building queries or filters.

children.name: Tag component has been used to create toggles that are also used for filtering. Two cases appear to be outliers that could be solved using other components: Subscription page: uses a long list of tags to provide filters; it could instead use standard multi-select drop-down filter (as-in global filter) Adopt: In one case, there is a toggle-able tag that is used to show or hide visitors w/ no events; it could instead use a toggle component or else include the option in the segment drop-down list?
children.characters:
Tag component has been used to create toggles that are also used for filtering.
Two cases appear to be outliers that could be solved using other components:
Subscription page: uses a long list of tags to provide filters; it could instead use standard multi-select drop-down filter (as-in global filter)
Adopt: In one case, there is a toggle-able tag that is used to show or hide visitors w/ no events; it could instead use a toggle component or else include the option in the segment drop-down list?
